      "title": "TLS Certificates"
    },
    {
      "description": "What symmetric encryption is and how TLS uses it for fast data transfer after the handshake.",
      "title": "Symmetric Encryption in TLS"
    },
    {
      "description": "What asymmetric (public/private key) encryption is and how TLS uses it during the handshake to exchange keys.",
      "title": "Asymmetric Encryption in TLS"
    },
    {
      "description": "What a proxy server is: an intermediary that sits between a client and a server and forwards requests.",
      "title": "What Is a Proxy?"
    },
    {
      "description": "What a forward proxy is: a proxy that acts on behalf of clients, often for filtering or privacy.",
      "title": "Forward Proxies"
    },
    {
      "description": "What a reverse proxy is: a proxy that sits in front of servers, often for load balancing or security.",
      "title": "Reverse Proxies"
    },
    {
      "description": "Common uses of proxies: access control, anonymity, logging, and traffic shaping.",
      "title": "Common Proxy Use Cases"
    },
    {
      "description": "What web caching is: storing copies of resources to serve future requests faster and reduce server load.",
      "title": "What Is Web Caching?"
    },
    {
      "description": "How browser caches store resources locally so repeat visits don't require new network requests.",
      "title": "Browser Cache"
    },
    {
