      "title": "Shared (Proxy) Caches"
    },
    {
      "description": "The concept of cache freshness: how a cached resource is considered valid for a specific period of time.",
      "title": "Cache Freshness"
    },
    {
      "description": "How stale caches are revalidated with the server using conditional requests and validators like ETags.",
      "title": "Cache Revalidation"
    },
    {
      "description": "What cookies are: small pieces of data a server sends to a client's browser to store and send back with future requests.",
      "title": "What Are Cookies?"
    },
    {
      "description": "How the Set-Cookie response header creates a cookie and the Cookie request header sends it back.",
      "title": "How Cookies Are Set and Sent"
